cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a new approach for assessing Wikipedia article quality based on individual edits rather than full documents. This involves using a main classifier and an auxiliary generative module to estimate the quality of each edit and generate a natural language description. This approach involves techniques from natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of generative models and language generation techniques also suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
